description:
Front:
T2 Yew Common (Taxus baccata) OPTION 1 - Fell to ground level and treat to prevent any further growth;
T2 Yew Common (Taxus baccata) OPTION 2 - Reduce the entire crown by 1.5-2m; 
S1 Yew Common (Taxus baccata) - Grind down the above stump 300mm below the ground level and remove all arisings.

Side of property:
G1 Various - Yew x 2 and Privet x 2 OPTION 1 - Fell to ground level and treat to prevent any further growth;
G1 Various - Yew x 2 and Privet x 2 OPTION 2- Reduce the height of all 4 by 1.5-2m all to the same level; reduce all growth growing towards both properties back to the main stems;
S2 Various - To Grind down all of the above stumps

Rear:
T3 Sycamore (Acer pseudoplatanus) - Full crown reduction; reduce the upper crown back to the previous points of reduction which approximately equates to 4-5m and 3-4m from the lower laterals aiming to blend with upper crown; remove the large epicormic growth from the main stem and remove the ivy and dead wood
